"Ancient River Diagram"

The oil painting of G water ripples series, Ancient River Diagram, shows a water rose representing yin-yang intergeneration and five-layer Tai Chi. One generates two, two generates three, and three generates everything. The concept of Tai Chi is a critical part in Chinese culture. What the painter wants to convey through this artwork is a relative view of the world. Everything appears in polar opposites and constantly changes. There is reality in the imaginary, the emptiness in the reality, and there is no black if no white and vice versa. At the same time, through the expression of water ripples, the painting explains the harmony and flexibility of nature.

#G水波纹潋滟系列
灵感起源于画家孙天骄在清华大学 进修油画写生时，对明城堡摩崖石刻之下 溪水的敏锐捕捉，此系列中后期的作品 加入孙天骄对人生感悟的哲思不断深刻。

《古河图》

G水波纹潋滟系列之《古河图》油画所绘的是 代表阴阳相生、五层太极的水玫瑰。 一生二、二生三、三生万物， 太极的概念在中国文化中至关重要。 画家想通过这幅艺术品传达的是相对的世界观， 一切事物都是成两极对立出现并不断变化的， 虚中有实、实中有虚，无黑无白； 同时通过水波纹的表现形式，阐述出大自然的圆融与变通。
